<br>
First, though while I'm appalled (I read those pages) and saddened about people's opinions who were using the exploit, thinking its ok to train others and ruin other people's fun, I'm not particularly surprised. I found myself more often agreeing with the way Gravely thinks, than not. And I'm sure, sooner or later, if Yendys hadn't started things, soemone else would of. Nyno is kind of silly to blame it all on Yendys, the only person really making FnF look bad are those people using the exploit *shrug* Yendys started the flame -- who cares. <br>
<br>
Secondly: I think its wrong to post internal posts from a guild board that were not public guild posts. Sorry, origional poster, but you're a fucktard for doing so, I don't care if you felt you needed to reveal it or not. That's private discussion between FNF folks. I would be livid if someone came to my boards and took private posts to a public soapbox forum. What am I saying. I've already been livid when people logged private discussions that should of stayed private and posted them publically.<br>
<br>
Its wrong. *shrug*<br>
<br>
That said.<br>
<br>
Look folks, most of the rules sony has are a pile of crap, but some of them make sense -- for instance, the rules about how you treat others. You should treat others with respect, and be considerate of them. Many agree kill-stealing is wrong. Many agree stealing camps is wrong though sony doesn't recognize camps. Sony has it in their rules that you shouldn't be griefing others (to paraphrase), and that you shouldn't monopolize mobs to the point others cannot hunt in an area.<br>
<br>
The people using the exploit are making Drunder practically unhuntable. I was barely able to kite the one day I was there, because they stole all the mobs from the top of the pit too -- and I had a full group. I cannot even imagine how bad it must of been for folks trying to exp down in the pit -- it would of been impossible, as their mobs were ripped away from them, or they were trained by the masses of mobs running around like wild lunatics. That pit can support 4 groups, not just one to two people or one group causing some bugged up faction war. I think that all this comes down to is being more considerate. Drunder has always been to my knowledge a fairly busy zone, at least during the hours I played, with several groups down in the pits, one in the kite room. Folks are supposed to share.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I just think the whole mentality over this issue, thinking its ok, even if you supposedly feel you haven't trained anyone, is sad. Very depressing really. Anyhow :P<br>
